/*
Generate a local self-signed cert/key pair for the ESP32 HTTPS server.

Why this format:
- Uses a Subject Alternative Name (SAN), which modern browsers expect.
- Writes to `main/secrets/Hidden/`, which matches the current project layout.
- Includes an example local DNS name plus an IP SAN for direct LAN testing.

Update `IP.2` in `main/secrets/Examples/openssl_local.cnf.example` to match your board's
current IP address if you want to browse to `https://<ip>/` directly.

Example command:

wsl bash -lc 'mkdir -p /mnt/c/<project_path>/main/secrets/Hidden && \
openssl req -x509 -nodes -newkey rsa:2048 -sha256 -days 365 \
-keyout /mnt/c/<project_path>/main/secrets/Hidden/server_key.pem \
-out /mnt/c/<project_path>/main/secrets/Hidden/server_cert.pem \
-config /mnt/c/<project_path>/main/secrets/Examples/openssl_local.cnf.example'
*/
